{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"One out of two of you women"},{"time":3000,"text":"will be impacted by cardiovascular disease"},{"time":5000,"text":"in your lifetime."},{"time":8000,"text":"So this is the leading killer of women."},{"time":12000,"text":"It's a closely held secret"},{"time":14000,"text":"for reasons I don't know."},{"time":17000,"text":"In addition to making this personal --"},{"time":20000,"text":"so we're going to talk about your relationship with your heart"},{"time":22000,"text":"and all women's relationship with their heart --"},{"time":25000,"text":"we're going to wax into the politics."},{"time":27000,"text":"Because the personal, as you know, is political."},{"time":30000,"text":"And not enough is being done about this."},{"time":33000,"text":"And as we have watched women"},{"time":35000,"text":"conquer breast cancer"},{"time":37000,"text":"through the breast cancer campaign,"},{"time":39000,"text":"this is what we need to do now with heart."}]},{"cues":[{"time":42000,"text":"Since 1984,"},{"time":44000,"text":"more women die in the U.S. than men."},{"time":48000,"text":"So where we used to think of heart disease"},{"time":51000,"text":"as being a man's problem primarily --"},{"time":54000,"text":"which that was never true,"},{"time":56000,"text":"but that was kind of how everybody thought in the 1950s and '60s,"},{"time":59000,"text":"and it was in all the textbooks."},{"time":61000,"text":"It's certainly what I learned when I was training."},{"time":64000,"text":"If we were to remain sexist, and that was not right,"},{"time":67000,"text":"but if we were going to go forward and be sexist,"},{"time":70000,"text":"it's actually a woman's disease."},{"time":72000,"text":"So it's a woman's disease now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":74000,"text":"And one of the things that you see"},{"time":76000,"text":"is that male line,"},{"time":78000,"text":"the mortality is going down, down, down, down, down."},{"time":80000,"text":"And you see the female line since 1984,"},{"time":83000,"text":"the gap is widening."},{"time":85000,"text":"More and more women, two, three, four times more women,"},{"time":88000,"text":"dying of heart disease than men."},{"time":91000,"text":"And that's too short of a time period"},{"time":93000,"text":"for all the different risk factors that we know"},{"time":95000,"text":"to change."},{"time":97000,"text":"So what this really suggested to us"},{"time":99000,"text":"at the national level"},{"time":101000,"text":"was that diagnostic and therapeutic strategies,"},{"time":105000,"text":"which had been developed in men, by men, for men"},{"time":108000,"text":"for the last 50 years --"},{"time":110000,"text":"and they work pretty well in men, don't they? --"},{"time":113000,"text":"weren't working so well for women."},{"time":116000,"text":"So that was a big wake-up call"},{"time":118000,"text":"in the 1980's."}]},{"cues":[{"time":120000,"text":"Heart disease kills more women"},{"time":123000,"text":"at all ages"},{"time":125000,"text":"than breast cancer."},{"time":127000,"text":"And the breast cancer campaign --"},{"time":129000,"text":"again, this is not a competition."},{"time":131000,"text":"We're trying to be as good as the breast cancer campaign."},{"time":134000,"text":"We need to be as good as the breast cancer campaign"},{"time":137000,"text":"to address this crisis."},{"time":139000,"text":"Now sometimes when people see this,"},{"time":141000,"text":"I hear this gasp."},{"time":143000,"text":"We can all think of someone,"},{"time":145000,"text":"often a young woman,"},{"time":147000,"text":"who has been impacted by breast cancer."},{"time":150000,"text":"We often can't think of a young woman"},{"time":152000,"text":"who has heart disease."},{"time":154000,"text":"I'm going to tell you why."},{"time":156000,"text":"Heart disease kills people,"},{"time":158000,"text":"often very quickly."},{"time":160000,"text":"So the first time heart disease strikes in women and men,"},{"time":163000,"text":"half of the time it's sudden cardiac death --"},{"time":166000,"text":"no opportunity to say good-bye,"},{"time":168000,"text":"no opportunity to take her to the chemotherapy,"},{"time":170000,"text":"no opportunity to help her pick out a wig."}]},{"cues":[{"time":173000,"text":"Breast cancer,"},{"time":175000,"text":"mortality is down to four percent."},{"time":178000,"text":"And that is the 40 years"},{"time":180000,"text":"that women have advocated."},{"time":184000,"text":"Betty Ford, Nancy Reagan stood up"},{"time":187000,"text":"and said, \"I'm a breast cancer survivor,\""},{"time":189000,"text":"and it was okay to talk about it."},{"time":191000,"text":"And then physicians have gone to bat."},{"time":193000,"text":"We've done the research."},{"time":195000,"text":"We have effective therapies now."},{"time":197000,"text":"Women are living longer than ever."},{"time":199000,"text":"That has to happen in heart disease, and it's time."},{"time":202000,"text":"It's not happening, and it's time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":207000,"text":"We owe an incredible debt of gratitude"},{"time":209000,"text":"to these two women."},{"time":211000,"text":"As Barbara depicted"},{"time":213000,"text":"in one of her amazing movies, \"Yentl,\""},{"time":217000,"text":"she portrayed a young woman"},{"time":219000,"text":"who wanted an education."},{"time":222000,"text":"And she wanted to study the Talmud."},{"time":224000,"text":"And so how did she get educated then?"},{"time":226000,"text":"She had to impersonate a man."},{"time":228000,"text":"She had to look like a man."},{"time":230000,"text":"She had to make other people believe that she looked like a man"},{"time":233000,"text":"and she could have the same rights"},{"time":235000,"text":"that the men had."},{"time":237000,"text":"Bernadine Healy, Dr. Healy,"},{"time":240000,"text":"was a cardiologist."},{"time":242000,"text":"And right around that time, in the 1980's,"},{"time":245000,"text":"that we saw women and heart disease deaths"},{"time":247000,"text":"going up, up, up, up, up,"},{"time":249000,"text":"she wrote an editorial"},{"time":251000,"text":"in the New England Journal of Medicine"},{"time":253000,"text":"and said, the Yentl syndrome."},{"time":256000,"text":"Women are dying of heart disease,"},{"time":258000,"text":"two, three, four times more than men."},{"time":261000,"text":"Mortality is not going down, it's going up."},{"time":264000,"text":"And she questioned,"},{"time":266000,"text":"she hypothesized,"},{"time":268000,"text":"is this a Yentl syndrome?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":270000,"text":"And here's what the story is."},{"time":272000,"text":"Is it because women don't look like men,"},{"time":275000,"text":"they don't look like that male-pattern heart disease"},{"time":278000,"text":"that we've spent the last 50 years understanding"},{"time":281000,"text":"and getting really good diagnostics"},{"time":283000,"text":"and really good therapeutics,"},{"time":285000,"text":"and therefore, they're not recognized for their heart disease."},{"time":287000,"text":"And they're just passed."},{"time":289000,"text":"They don't get treated, they don't get detected,"},{"time":292000,"text":"they don't get the benefit of all the modern medicines."}]},{"cues":[{"time":295000,"text":"Doctor Healy then subsequently became"},{"time":297000,"text":"the first female director"},{"time":299000,"text":"of our National Institutes of Health."},{"time":301000,"text":"And this is the biggest biomedical enterprise research"},{"time":304000,"text":"in the world."},{"time":306000,"text":"And it funds a lot of my research."},{"time":308000,"text":"It funds research all over the place."},{"time":310000,"text":"It was a very big deal"},{"time":312000,"text":"for her to become director."},{"time":314000,"text":"And she started,"},{"time":316000,"text":"in the face of a lot of controversy,"},{"time":318000,"text":"the Women's Health Initiative."},{"time":320000,"text":"And every woman in the room here"},{"time":322000,"text":"has benefited from that Women's Health Initiative."},{"time":324000,"text":"It told us about hormone replacement therapy."},{"time":327000,"text":"It's informed us about osteoporosis."},{"time":329000,"text":"It informed us about breast cancer, colon cancer in women."},{"time":332000,"text":"So a tremendous fund of knowledge"},{"time":335000,"text":"despite, again,"},{"time":337000,"text":"that so many people told her not to do it,"},{"time":339000,"text":"it was too expensive."},{"time":341000,"text":"And the under-reading was women aren't worth it."},{"time":344000,"text":"She was like, \"Nope. Sorry. Women are worth it.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":347000,"text":"Well there was a little piece of that Women's Health Initiative"},{"time":350000,"text":"that went to National Heart, Lung, and Blood Institute,"},{"time":352000,"text":"which is the cardiology part of the NIH."},{"time":355000,"text":"And we got to do the WISE study --"},{"time":357000,"text":"and the WISE stands for Women's Ischemia Syndrome Evaluation --"},{"time":361000,"text":"and I have chaired this study for the last 15 years."},{"time":363000,"text":"It was a study to specifically ask,"},{"time":366000,"text":"what's going on with women?"},{"time":368000,"text":"Why are more and more women dying"},{"time":370000,"text":"of ischemic heart disease?"},{"time":372000,"text":"So in the WISE, 15 years ago,"},{"time":375000,"text":"we started out and said, \"Well wow, there's a couple of key observations"},{"time":378000,"text":"and we should probably follow up on that.\""},{"time":380000,"text":"And our colleagues in Washington, D.C."},{"time":383000,"text":"had recently published"},{"time":386000,"text":"that when women have heart attacks and die,"},{"time":389000,"text":"compared to men who have heart attacks and die --"},{"time":392000,"text":"and again, this is millions of people,"},{"time":394000,"text":"happening every day --"},{"time":397000,"text":"women, in their fatty plaque --"},{"time":399000,"text":"and this is their coronary artery,"},{"time":401000,"text":"so the main blood supply going into the heart muscle --"},{"time":403000,"text":"women erode,"},{"time":405000,"text":"men explode."},{"time":408000,"text":"You're going to find some interesting analogies"},{"time":410000,"text":"in this physiology."}]},{"cues":[{"time":412000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":415000,"text":"So I'll describe the male-pattern heart attack first."},{"time":418000,"text":"Hollywood heart attack. Ughhhh."},{"time":420000,"text":"Horrible chest pain."},{"time":422000,"text":"EKG goes pbbrrhh,"},{"time":424000,"text":"so the doctors can see this hugely abnormal EKG."},{"time":427000,"text":"There's a big clot in the middle of the artery."},{"time":429000,"text":"And they go up to the cath lab"},{"time":431000,"text":"and boom, boom, boom get rid of the clot."},{"time":433000,"text":"That's a man heart attack."},{"time":435000,"text":"Some women have those heart attacks,"},{"time":437000,"text":"but a whole bunch of women have this kind of heart attack,"},{"time":439000,"text":"where it erodes,"},{"time":441000,"text":"doesn't completely fill with clot, symptoms are subtle,"},{"time":444000,"text":"EKG findings are different --"},{"time":446000,"text":"female-pattern."},{"time":448000,"text":"So what do you think happens to these gals?"},{"time":451000,"text":"They're often not recognized, sent home."},{"time":453000,"text":"I'm not sure what it was. Might have been gas."}]},{"cues":[{"time":456000,"text":"So we picked up on that"},{"time":458000,"text":"and we said, \"You know, we now have the ability"},{"time":461000,"text":"to look inside human beings"},{"time":464000,"text":"with these special catheters called IVUS:"},{"time":466000,"text":"intravascular ultrasound.\""},{"time":468000,"text":"And we said, \"We're going to hypothesize"},{"time":471000,"text":"that the fatty plaque in women"},{"time":474000,"text":"is actually probably different,"},{"time":476000,"text":"and deposited differently, than men.\""},{"time":478000,"text":"And because of the common knowledge"},{"time":482000,"text":"of how women and men get fat."},{"time":484000,"text":"When we watch people become obese,"},{"time":488000,"text":"where do men get fat?"},{"time":491000,"text":"Right here, it's just a focal -- right there."},{"time":495000,"text":"Where do women get fat?"},{"time":498000,"text":"All over."},{"time":500000,"text":"Cellulite here, cellulite here."},{"time":503000,"text":"So we said, \"Look, women look like they're pretty good"},{"time":505000,"text":"about putting kind of the garbage away,"},{"time":507000,"text":"smoothly putting it away."},{"time":509000,"text":"Men just have to dump it in a single area.\""},{"time":512000,"text":"So we said, \"Let's look at these.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":514000,"text":"And so the yellow is the fatty plaque,"},{"time":517000,"text":"and panel A is a man."},{"time":519000,"text":"And you can see, it's lumpy bumpy."},{"time":521000,"text":"He's got a beer belly in his coronary arteries."},{"time":524000,"text":"Panel B is the woman, very smooth."},{"time":526000,"text":"She's just laid it down nice and tidy."},{"time":528000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":530000,"text":"And if you did that angiogram,"},{"time":532000,"text":"which is the red,"},{"time":534000,"text":"you can see the man's disease."},{"time":536000,"text":"So 50 years"},{"time":538000,"text":"of honing and crafting these angiograms,"},{"time":540000,"text":"we easily recognize"},{"time":542000,"text":"male-pattern disease."},{"time":544000,"text":"Kind of hard to see that female-pattern disease."},{"time":546000,"text":"So that was a discovery."},{"time":548000,"text":"Now what are the implications of that?"},{"time":551000,"text":"Well once again, women get the angiogram"},{"time":553000,"text":"and nobody can tell that they have a problem."}]},{"cues":[{"time":556000,"text":"So we are working now on a non-invasive --"},{"time":559000,"text":"again, these are all invasive studies."},{"time":561000,"text":"Ideally you would love to do all this non-invasively."},{"time":564000,"text":"And again, 50 years"},{"time":566000,"text":"of good non-invasive stress testing,"},{"time":568000,"text":"we're pretty good at recognizing male-pattern disease"},{"time":570000,"text":"with stress tests."},{"time":572000,"text":"So this is cardiac magnetic resonance imaging."},{"time":574000,"text":"We're doing this at the Cedars-Sinai Heart Institute"},{"time":577000,"text":"in the Women's Heart Center."},{"time":579000,"text":"We selected this for the research."},{"time":582000,"text":"This is not in your community hospital,"},{"time":584000,"text":"but we would hope to translate this."},{"time":586000,"text":"And we're about two and a half years"},{"time":588000,"text":"into a five-year study."}]},{"cues":[{"time":590000,"text":"This was the only modality"},{"time":592000,"text":"that can see the inner lining of the heart."},{"time":594000,"text":"And if you look carefully, you can see"},{"time":596000,"text":"that there's a black blush right there."},{"time":598000,"text":"And that is microvascular obstruction."},{"time":601000,"text":"The syndrome, the female-pattern"},{"time":604000,"text":"now is called microvascular coronary dysfunction, or obstruction."},{"time":608000,"text":"The second reason we really liked MRI"},{"time":611000,"text":"is that there's no radiation."},{"time":613000,"text":"So unlike the CAT scans, X-rays, thalliums,"},{"time":616000,"text":"for women"},{"time":618000,"text":"whose breast is in the way"},{"time":620000,"text":"of looking at the heart,"},{"time":622000,"text":"every time we order something that has even a small amount of radiation,"},{"time":625000,"text":"we say, \"Do we really need that test?\""},{"time":627000,"text":"So we're very excited about M.R."},{"time":629000,"text":"You can't go and order it yet,"},{"time":631000,"text":"but this is an area of active inquiry"},{"time":633000,"text":"where actually studying women"},{"time":635000,"text":"is going to advance the field for women and men."}]},{"cues":[{"time":639000,"text":"What are the downstream consequences"},{"time":642000,"text":"then, when female-pattern heart disease"},{"time":645000,"text":"is not recognized?"},{"time":647000,"text":"This is a figure"},{"time":649000,"text":"from an editorial that I published"},{"time":651000,"text":"in the European Heart Journal this last summer."},{"time":654000,"text":"And it was just a pictogram"},{"time":656000,"text":"to sort of show"},{"time":658000,"text":"why more women are dying of heart disease,"},{"time":660000,"text":"despite these good treatments"},{"time":662000,"text":"that we know and we have work."},{"time":665000,"text":"And when the woman"},{"time":667000,"text":"has male-pattern disease --"},{"time":669000,"text":"so she looks like Barbara in the movie --"},{"time":672000,"text":"they get treated."},{"time":674000,"text":"And when you have female-pattern and you look like a woman,"},{"time":677000,"text":"as Barbara does here with her husband,"},{"time":680000,"text":"they don't get the treatment."},{"time":682000,"text":"These are our life-saving treatments."},{"time":684000,"text":"And those little red boxes are deaths."},{"time":687000,"text":"So those are the consequences."},{"time":689000,"text":"And that is female-pattern"},{"time":691000,"text":"and why we think the Yentl syndrome"},{"time":693000,"text":"actually is explaining"},{"time":695000,"text":"a lot of these gaps."}]},{"cues":[{"time":698000,"text":"There's been wonderful news also"},{"time":701000,"text":"about studying women,"},{"time":703000,"text":"finally, in heart disease."},{"time":705000,"text":"And one of the the cutting-edge areas"},{"time":707000,"text":"that we're just incredibly excited about"},{"time":709000,"text":"is stem cell therapy."},{"time":711000,"text":"If you ask, what is the big difference"},{"time":714000,"text":"between women and men physiologically?"},{"time":716000,"text":"Why are there women and men?"},{"time":719000,"text":"Because women bring new life into the world."},{"time":722000,"text":"That's all stem cells."},{"time":724000,"text":"So we hypothesized"},{"time":726000,"text":"that female stem cells might be better"},{"time":729000,"text":"at identifying the injury,"},{"time":732000,"text":"doing some cellular repair"},{"time":734000,"text":"or even producing new organs,"},{"time":736000,"text":"which is one of the things"},{"time":738000,"text":"that we're trying to do with stem cell therapy."},{"time":741000,"text":"These are female and male stem cells."},{"time":744000,"text":"And if you had an injured organ,"},{"time":746000,"text":"if you had a heart attack"},{"time":748000,"text":"and we wanted to repair that injured area,"},{"time":751000,"text":"do you want those robust,"},{"time":753000,"text":"plentiful stem cells on the top?"},{"time":756000,"text":"Or do you want these guys,"},{"time":758000,"text":"that look like they're out to lunch?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":760000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":762000,"text":"And some of our investigative teams"},{"time":765000,"text":"have demonstrated"},{"time":767000,"text":"that female stem cells --"},{"time":769000,"text":"and this is in animals"},{"time":771000,"text":"and increasingly we're showing this in humans --"},{"time":773000,"text":"that female stem cells,"},{"time":775000,"text":"when put even into a male body,"},{"time":777000,"text":"do better than male stem cells"},{"time":780000,"text":"going into a male body."},{"time":782000,"text":"One of the things that we say"},{"time":784000,"text":"about all of this female physiology --"},{"time":786000,"text":"because again, as much as we're talking about women and heart disease,"},{"time":789000,"text":"women do, on average,"},{"time":791000,"text":"have better longevity than men --"},{"time":793000,"text":"is that unfolding the secrets of female physiology"},{"time":796000,"text":"and understanding that"},{"time":798000,"text":"is going to help men and women."},{"time":801000,"text":"So this is not a zero-sum game in anyway."}]},{"cues":[{"time":804000,"text":"Okay, so here's where we started."},{"time":806000,"text":"And remember, paths crossed in 1984,"},{"time":810000,"text":"and more and more women"},{"time":812000,"text":"were dying of cardiovascular disease."},{"time":814000,"text":"What has happened in the last 15 years with this work?"},{"time":817000,"text":"We are bending the curve."},{"time":819000,"text":"We're bending the curve."},{"time":821000,"text":"So just like the breast cancer story,"},{"time":824000,"text":"doing research, getting awareness going,"},{"time":827000,"text":"it works, you just have to get it going."},{"time":830000,"text":"Now are we happy with this?"},{"time":832000,"text":"We still have two to three more women dying for every man."}]},{"cues":[{"time":835000,"text":"And I would propose,"},{"time":837000,"text":"with the better longevity"},{"time":839000,"text":"that women have overall,"},{"time":841000,"text":"that women probably should theoretically do better,"},{"time":843000,"text":"if we could just get treated."},{"time":845000,"text":"So this is where we are,"},{"time":848000,"text":"but we have a long row to hoe."},{"time":850000,"text":"We've worked on this for 15 years."},{"time":852000,"text":"And I've told you, we've been working on male-pattern heart disease"},{"time":855000,"text":"for 50 years."},{"time":857000,"text":"So we're 35 years behind."},{"time":859000,"text":"And we'd like to think it's not going to take 35 years."},{"time":862000,"text":"And in fact, it probably won't."},{"time":864000,"text":"But we cannot stop now."},{"time":866000,"text":"Too many lives are at stake."}]},{"cues":[{"time":869000,"text":"So what do we need to do?"},{"time":872000,"text":"You now, hopefully, have a more personal relationship"},{"time":874000,"text":"with your heart."},{"time":876000,"text":"Women have heard the call"},{"time":878000,"text":"for breast cancer"},{"time":880000,"text":"and they have come out"},{"time":882000,"text":"for awareness campaigns."},{"time":884000,"text":"The women are very good about getting mammograms now."},{"time":887000,"text":"And women do fundraising."},{"time":889000,"text":"Women participate."},{"time":891000,"text":"They have put their money where their mouth is"},{"time":893000,"text":"and they have done advocacy and they have joined campaigns."},{"time":896000,"text":"This is what we need to do with heart disease now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":899000,"text":"And it's political."},{"time":901000,"text":"Women's health, from a federal funding standpoint,"},{"time":904000,"text":"sometimes it's popular,"},{"time":906000,"text":"sometimes it's not so popular."},{"time":909000,"text":"So we have these feast and famine cycles."},{"time":911000,"text":"So I implore you"},{"time":913000,"text":"to join the Red Dress Campaign"},{"time":915000,"text":"in this fundraising."},{"time":917000,"text":"Breast cancer, as we said,"},{"time":919000,"text":"kills women,"},{"time":921000,"text":"but heart disease kills a whole bunch more."},{"time":924000,"text":"So if we can be as good as breast cancer"},{"time":926000,"text":"and give women this new charge,"},{"time":928000,"text":"we have a lot of lives to save."}]},{"cues":[{"time":930000,"text":"So thank you for your attention."}]},{"cues":[{"time":932000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}